Class Connection

java.lang.Object
  main.Connection
Direct Known Subclasses:
ClientConnection, ServerConnection
public class Connection
extends java.lang.Object

A custom class to handle the incoming and outgoing Packets in a Socket. There are two subclasses, ServerConnection and ClientConnection which handle the Sockets on the Server and Client side respectively.

Nested Class Summary
static class Connection.Command
           
 class Connection.ConnectionReader
          ConnectionReader continuously reads in the next Packet from the incoming stream and processes it.
 class Connection.ConnectionWriter
          ConnectionWriter continuously takes Packets from the messageQueue to write to the outgoing stream.
